Bug: Initializing `max` to `0` fails for arrays where all numbers are negative or where the actual max is less than 0.

Fix: Initialize `max` to the first array element.

```javascript
function findMax(arr) {
  if (arr.length === 0) return undefined;
  let max = arr[0];
  for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] > max) max = arr[i];
  }
  return max;
}
```

